extends layout.pug

block content 
  article.grid-container.portfolio-intro
    div
 
      h1 My portfolio Web App

      p.lead.text-light
        | This portfolio app showcases my web development projects using a clean and modern design. 
        | It features a homepage with an overview of my projects, an about page, 
        | and a project page for each project that includes a description, technologies used, live link, and GitHub repository link. 
        | The app is built using Node.js, Express.js, and Pug, and includes error handling and middleware for a seamless user experience.
  article.grid-container.portfolio-index
    
    .grid-x.grid-margin-x.small-up-2.medium-up-2.large-up-3

      //- Use the Pug `each` iterator to create a projet img, title and link in the markup for each of the projects you are showcasing.  
      .row
        each project in projects
          .col-md-4
            .cell
              a(href=`${project.liveLink}`)
                img.thumbnail(src=`${project.imageUrls[0]}`)
                h5= project.name

      //- Use a combination of interpolation and template literals as needed to dynamically generate the the routes in the href, as well as the img's src and the projects title.
      
      //- Here's what the Pug for each project example should look like. 

      .cell
        a(href='#')
          img.thumbnail(src='https://placehold.it/550x550')
          h5 Title
      
      
